Sentencas: Low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs) have attracted much attention for their long-term stability, short start-up time, and economic competitiveness.
Titulo: A Highly Active Perovskite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ

Sentencas: Development of a high electrochemical active cathode for the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) is the key to LT-SOFCs.
Titulo: A Highly Active Perovskite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ

Sentencas: In this study, a cubic perovskite BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-delta (BCFSc) is synthesized and investigated.
Titulo: A Highly Active Perovskite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ

Sentencas: It exhibits extremely low polarization resistances (e.g., 0.03 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C) in symmetric cell using Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) as the electrolyte, indicating an excellent ORR catalytic activity.
Titulo: A Highly Active Perovskite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ

Sentencas: A maximum output power density of 1446 mW cm(-2) is achieved at 600 degrees C for a single cell with an anode functional layer, which is much larger than the one without it (1045 mW cm(-2)).
Titulo: A Highly Active Perovskite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ

Sentencas: The favorable performance enables BCFSc to be a candidate cathode for LT-SOFCs.
Titulo: A Highly Active Perovskite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ
